text This distinct communion, then, of the saints with the Father, Son, and Spirit, is very plain in the Scripture; but yet it may admit of farther demonstration. Only this caution I must lay in beforehand:-- whatever is affirmed in the pursuit of this truth, it is done with relation to the explanation ensuing, in the beginning of the next chapter.

text The way and means, then, on the part of the saints, whereby in Christ they enjoy communion with God, are all the spiritual and holy actings
